# Persistent Memory

**Plugin memory lives at `.cursor/memory/` (gitignored).** Read from and write to
`.cursor/memory/` when this plugin is installed — matching
`session-state` / `memory-extraction` and the `sessionStart` memory-index hook.
The index is `.cursor/memory/MEMORY.md`.

### Read at session start
- Open `.cursor/memory/MEMORY.md` first; read entries that touch the request.
- If memory cites a path or flag about to be acted on, verify it still exists before recommending.
- If memory contradicts the code, trust the code and update or remove the stale memory.

### Write durable facts only
Save non-obvious facts a future session would otherwise relearn: feedback corrections/confirmations, project decisions (absolute dates), user preferences, external system pointers.

### Do not write
Code patterns and architecture (derivable), git history, debugging recipes, in-progress task state (use plans/todos).

### File mechanics
- One memory per file under `.cursor/memory/` with frontmatter: `name`, `description`, and `type` **nested under `metadata`** (a top-level `type:` is wrong — see memory-extraction).
- One line per entry in `MEMORY.md` (≤150 chars). Update before duplicating. Keep the index ≤200 lines.
